[SN]TITLE[SN]
Snow, ice and wind warnings for Wales issued by Met Office

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Yellow "be aware" warnings of snow, ice and wind across Wales have been issued by the Met Office.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Snow and ice are expected to affect Conwy, Denbighshire, Flintshire, Gwynedd, Anglesey, Wrexham and Powys from 00:05 GMT on Wednesday.
Gusts up to 70 mph are forecast for Ceredigion, Carmarthenshire, Swansea and Pembrokeshire from 08:00.
The Met Office warned of "difficult driving conditions" and "travel disruption" in rush hour.
Up to 10cm (3.9in) of snow was forecast in areas above 200m (650ft) with icy stretches on untreated roads and pavements also likely.
The warnings for ice and snow cover the period up to 10:00, with the one for wind lasting until midday.
